  "author_association": "MEMBER",
  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "We currently have an `ERC20Basic` interface, which is a subset of `ERC20`, and the respective implementations `BasicToken` and `StandardToken`. I want to propose to remove that distinction and have only `ERC20` and `StandardToken`.\r\n\r\nOne argument in favor is to simplify our contract offering for developer/user experience purposes.\r\n\r\nAnother argument in favor is that tokens created with OpenZeppelin should be properly `ERC20` compliant, and `BasicToken` possibly encourages the deployment of non-`ERC20` tokens.",
